@page
@model Northwind.Web.Pages.SuppliersModel
@*This is a Razor page in an ASP.NET Core application. It displays a table of supplier company names.

Here's a breakdown:

@page indicates that this is a Razor page.

@model Northwind.Web.Pages.SuppliersModel specifies the model class that provides data for this page.

The HTML code creates a table with a header row containing "Company Name".

If the Suppliers property of the model is not null, the code loops through each supplier name and 
adds a table row with the name.

In essence, this code snippet is a simple Razor page that displays a list of supplier company names, 
assuming the data is provided by the SuppliersModel class.
*@

<div class="row">
    <h1 class="display-2">Suppliers</h1>
    <table class="table">
        <thead class="thead-inverse">
            <tr>
                <th>Company Name</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            @if (Model.Suppliers is not null)
            {
                @foreach (string name in Model.Suppliers)
                {
                    <tr>
                        <td>@name</td>
                    </tr>
                }
            }
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
